A BILL FOR AN ACT
To re-appropriate Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) under Public
Law No. 21-10, Section 2(G), for operational expenses of the Office
of the Mayor of the Municipality of Rota.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE 24TH NORTHERN MARIANAS
COMMONWEALTH LEGISLATURE:
1 Section 1. Findings and Purpose. The Legislature finds that, pursuant to
2 Public Law No. 21-10, the annual casino license fee paid for the sixth year is to be
3 distributed in accordance with 4 CMC § 2307. Specifically, 4 CMC § 2307(a)
4 provides that Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) shall be allocated to the First
5 Senatorial District. Further, Section 2(G) of Public Law No. 21-10 designates Fifty
6 Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00) from this allocation for partial payment to Sun
7 Palace for lodging expenses incurred by Rota patients, under the expenditure
8 authority of the Secretary of Finance.
9 The Legislature further finds that, according to a funding certification
10 issued by the Department of Finance on October 29, 2024, the Fifty Thousand
11 Dollars ($50,000.00) allocated under Section 2(G) of Public Law No. 21-10
12 remained unencumbered and available in Business Unit No. 7193B.

